SENATE BILL 2211
By Johnson
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 5;
Title 6; Title 7; Title 9; Title 12 and Title 13, relative
to local government contracts.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 7-51-904(b), is amended by deleting
the language "at least seven (7) days prior to the date set for such meeting" and substituting "at
least ten (10) days prior to the date set for such meeting".
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it,
and applies to contracts, leases, and lease-purchase agreements executed, renewed, modified,
or extended on or after such date.
